00:54:54,186 --> 00:54:58,357
Yours, mine and everyone else's
in this room.

708
00:54:58,427 --> 00:55:03,027
But it is my class.
Hamilton, Brandt, Cornfeld, up front!

709
00:55:03,097 --> 00:55:06,128
Mr. Spicoli has been kind enough
to bring us a snack.

710
00:55:06,208 --> 00:55:09,269
Be my guest.
Help yourselves.

711
00:55:10,408 --> 00:55:13,208
Get a good one.

712
00:55:18,279 --> 00:55:21,410
- Mike? Mike? Hi.
- Hi.

713
00:55:21,490 --> 00:55:24,420
- How you doing?
- Good. How are you?

714
00:55:24,490 --> 00:55:27,951
I hate walking. I have to walk
every day. It's such a drag.

715
00:55:28,031 --> 00:55:30,050
Why don't you get a ride
with somebody?

716
00:55:30,130 --> 00:55:33,220
Sometimes I ride with my brother,
but he works mornings.

717
00:55:33,300 --> 00:55:37,002
- Then he drives himself to school.
- What a guy!

718
00:55:37,072 --> 00:55:41,342
Listen, Mark Ratner
really likes you.

719
00:55:41,412 --> 00:55:45,942
- Do you like him?
- Mark is really nice.

720
00:55:46,012 --> 00:55:48,243
But I think I like you.

721
00:55:58,994 --> 00:56:02,434
Well, uh... this is me.

722
00:56:03,704 --> 00:56:06,366
- Do you have any iced tea?
- Yeah, sure.

723
00:56:06,436 --> 00:56:08,406
Come on in.

724
00:56:11,406 --> 00:56:14,576
The annuals are coming out
pretty soon.

725
00:56:14,646 --> 00:56:18,347
- You gonna get one?
- I don't know.

726
00:56:18,417 --> 00:56:22,687
Oh, come on. Aren't you curious
to see how your picture turned out?

727
00:56:22,757 --> 00:56:25,388
- I know what I look like.
- I know.

728
00:56:25,458 --> 00:56:28,857
But it's nice to have pictures
of your friends and stuff.

729
00:56:28,927 --> 00:56:31,798
I don't know. Maybe.
It's no big deal.

730
00:56:31,868 --> 00:56:34,928
I probably will.

731
00:56:34,998 --> 00:56:36,940
Must be nice having a pool.

732
00:56:37,010 --> 00:56:39,769
- You want to go swimming?
- Yeah, sure.

733
00:56:39,839 --> 00:56:43,210
- I'm going to go change, okay?
- Yeah.

734
00:56:43,280 --> 00:56:44,370
Okay, great.

735
00:56:54,261 --> 00:56:56,552
This is great iced tea.

736
00:56:59,901 --> 00:57:01,992
- Come on.
- Huh?

737
00:57:02,062 --> 00:57:04,332
Brad keeps his stuff
in the change room.

738
00:57:16,454 --> 00:57:18,443
- This is nice.
- Yeah?

739
00:57:18,513 --> 00:57:22,515
- Yeah.
- These'll fit you.

740
00:57:34,606 --> 00:57:38,366
- You're really a good kisser.
- Yeah?

741
00:57:38,436 --> 00:57:40,467
So are you.

742
00:57:47,318 --> 00:57:50,378
You want to take off
your clothes, Mike?

743
00:57:50,458 --> 00:57:53,189
You first.

744
00:57:53,259 --> 00:57:56,959
Both of us at the same time.

745
00:57:57,029 --> 00:57:58,959
Okay.

746
00:58:42,645 --> 00:58:44,705
Are you okay?

747
00:58:44,785 --> 00:58:46,845
Ahh.

748
00:58:46,915 --> 00:58:50,216
I think I came.
Didn't you feel it?

749
00:58:51,286 --> 00:58:52,776
Yeah. I guess I did.

750
00:58:56,297 --> 00:58:58,926
I gotta go, Stacy.

751
00:58:58,996 --> 00:59:01,557
I've really gotta go.

752
00:59:15,679 --> 00:59:18,618
- See ya.
- Bye.

753
00:59:19,819 --> 00:59:23,050
Linda, how long does Doug take?

754
00:59:23,130 --> 00:59:26,031
- Doug takes forever.
- Come on.

755
00:59:26,101 --> 00:59:29,790
He takes, uh... 20 to 30 minutes.

756
00:59:29,870 --> 00:59:33,201
I thought you said
he took 30 to 40 minutes.

757
00:59:33,271 --> 00:59:36,901
That's right. I'm sorry.
I meant 30 to 40 minutes.

758
00:59:36,971 --> 00:59:39,002
How long did Damone take?

759
00:59:39,072 --> 00:59:44,513
Damone took, uh...
15 to 20 minutes.

760
00:59:44,583 --> 00:59:48,352
That's not bad for a high school boy.

761
01:00:00,034 --> 01:00:02,764
- Mike! Hi!
- Hi.

762
01:00:02,835 --> 01:00:06,036
- God, I haven't seen you for a while.
- Yeah.

763
01:00:06,106 --> 01:00:09,596
- In a hurry. Got stuff I gotta do.
- I'm in a hurry too.

764
01:00:09,676 --> 01:00:12,736
- I just thought I'd say hi to you.
- Hi.

765
01:00:15,947 --> 01:00:18,856
Hamilton, I'll take over
the fryer for a while.

766
01:00:18,916 --> 01:00:22,218
Those boys at I.B.M. Ordered a stack
of those Catch-of-the-Day boxes.

767
01:00:22,288 --> 01:00:26,697
- I told them you would personally
deliver them within the hour.
- Aye, aye, sir.

768
01:00:34,769 --> 01:00:38,069
Hamilton, come over here.

769
01:00:40,750 --> 01:00:43,740
- What are you doing?
- I'm changing.

770
01:00:43,820 --> 01:00:45,779
You took off your Captain Hook uniform.

771
01:00:45,849 --> 01:00:49,750
I thought I'd put street clothes on
for the drive to I.B.M.

772
01:00:49,820 --> 01:00:51,761
The uniform's uncomfortable.

773
01:00:51,821 --> 01:00:56,261
You're going there as a representative
of Captain Hook Fish and Chips.

774
01:00:56,331 --> 01:00:59,632
Part of our image, part of our appeal
is that uniform. You know that.

775
01:00:59,702 --> 01:01:02,102
You want me to put
the stuff back on?

776
01:01:02,172 --> 01:01:04,762
Yes, I do. Show a little pride.

777
01:01:04,842 --> 01:01:07,473
Aye, aye, sir.

778
01:02:18,191 --> 01:02:23,183
Dina, can you honestly tell me
that you forgot?

779
01:02:23,263 --> 01:02:27,293
Forgot the magnetism of Robin Zander
or the charisma of Rick Nielsen?

780
01:02:27,363 --> 01:02:30,353
- That's kid stuff.
- Kid stuff?

781
01:02:45,615 --> 01:02:48,555
Can I talk to you for a sec?

782
01:02:48,625 --> 01:02:53,497
Stacy, I'm doing business.
Call me tonight, all right?

783
01:02:53,567 --> 01:02:57,466
No. I've gotta talk to you now.
Okay?

784
01:02:59,937 --> 01:03:01,927
Don't go away.

785
01:03:02,007 --> 01:03:03,977
Look at 'em.

786
01:03:05,938 --> 01:03:09,508
I hope this is important
because I could be blowin' a big deal.

787
01:03:09,578 --> 01:03:11,609
Mike, I just...

788
01:03:11,679 --> 01:03:15,118
I just want you to know
that I'm pregnant.

789
01:03:18,519 --> 01:03:21,020
How do you know it's mine?
We only did it once.

790
01:03:21,090 --> 01:03:24,060
I haven't been with anybody else.
I know it's yours.

791
01:03:24,130 --> 01:03:26,390
Jesus!
It was your idea.

792
01:03:26,470 --> 01:03:29,230
You wanted to do it.
You wanted it more than I did.

793
01:03:29,300 --> 01:03:31,601
No.
Take that back.

794
01:03:34,040 --> 01:03:37,872
All right.
I take it back.

795
01:03:37,942 --> 01:03:41,282
Look, we gotta do somethin' about it.

796
01:03:41,352 --> 01:03:44,442
I mean, uh,
we gotta get an abortion.

797
01:03:44,522 --> 01:03:48,283
My brother Art got his girlfriend
one once. It's simple.

798
01:03:48,353 --> 01:03:53,384
- It's no big deal.
- Yeah. I got that planned.

799
01:03:53,464 --> 01:03:57,394
It's going to cost $150
at the Free Clinic.

800
01:03:57,464 --> 01:04:01,165
Doesn't sound free to me.

801
01:04:01,235 --> 01:04:03,904
I suppose you want me
to pay for it.

802
01:04:03,974 --> 01:04:06,965
Half, okay?
And a ride to the clinic.

803
01:04:07,046 --> 01:04:09,516
Seventy-five dollars and a ride.

804
01:04:11,016 --> 01:04:12,576
Okay.

805
01:04:13,756 --> 01:04:16,916
Okay. Thanks.

806
01:04:19,026 --> 01:04:20,998
Thank you.

807
01:04:22,058 --> 01:04:24,027
God.

808
01:04:25,727 --> 01:04:28,668
Rick, I need that $50 you owe me.

809
01:04:28,738 --> 01:04:33,269
- Don't have it.
- I know times are tight,
but I really need it.

810
01:04:33,338 --> 01:04:37,509
- Don't have it now.
- When you needed the tickets,
I got 'em for you.

811
01:04:37,579 --> 01:04:39,950
So close to stage
you probably scared the band.

812
01:04:40,020 --> 01:04:42,450
I'm not the Bank of America.

813
01:04:42,520 --> 01:04:45,580
I know you're not the Bank of America,
but I need my $50.

814
01:04:45,650 --> 01:04:49,420
- How about Thursday?
- Thursday's too late.
I need it tonight.

815
01:04:49,490 --> 01:04:52,052
Can't give you what I don't have.

816
01:04:52,132 --> 01:04:56,831
Just forget about it.
I'll get it from you Thursday, okay?

817
01:04:56,901 --> 01:04:59,302
All right.
See ya.

818
01:05:33,745 --> 01:05:35,607
Is Mike there?
This is Stacy.

819
01:05:35,677 --> 01:05:37,707
Hold on, please.

820
01:05:39,177 --> 01:05:42,118
Stacy, he says he's helping
his father in the garage.

821
01:05:42,188 --> 01:05:43,617
He'll call you later.

822
01:05:47,057 --> 01:05:48,748
Brad!

823
01:05:48,828 --> 01:05:51,189
Wait a second.

824
01:05:54,329 --> 01:05:57,059
- Yeah, this is it.
We're just going bowling.
- Okay.

825
01:05:57,139 --> 01:05:59,069
- Thanks a lot.
- See you later.

826
01:05:59,139 --> 01:06:01,070
Okay.

827
01:06:15,091 --> 01:06:18,892
- How we doing in here?
Debbie, you ready to leave?
- Yes. Thank you.

828
01:06:20,293 --> 01:06:22,952
Stacy, I can't let you go
unless you have a ride home.

829
01:06:23,032 --> 01:06:28,473
- Oh. I told my boyfriend
to meet me downstairs.
- Okay.

830
01:06:28,533 --> 01:06:30,523
Thanks.

831
01:06:39,515 --> 01:06:41,545
Brad.

832
01:06:45,225 --> 01:06:47,655
Since when do you
go bowling anyway?

833
01:06:47,725 --> 01:06:50,957
Okay, Brad.
Please don't tell Mom and Dad.

834
01:06:51,027 --> 01:06:54,296
Come on!
Who did it?

835
01:06:58,737 --> 01:07:01,677
You're not gonna tell me, are you?

836
01:07:04,848 --> 01:07:08,649
Okay.
It'll just be your secret.

837
01:07:08,719 --> 01:07:10,649
Okay.

838
01:07:10,719 --> 01:07:14,048
- You all right?
- Yeah.

839
01:07:14,118 --> 01:07:16,179
Come on.

840
01:07:17,959 --> 01:07:20,550
- You hungry?
- Yeah.

841
01:07:24,800 --> 01:07:28,131
I told you to tell Mike to pay for it.
Why didn't you tell him?

842
01:07:28,201 --> 01:07:30,571
Linda, he didn't show up.

843
01:07:30,641 --> 01:07:32,370
That little prick!

844
01:07:32,440 --> 01:07:35,412
I called his house.

845
01:07:35,482 --> 01:07:39,973
His mother told me he was
in the garage helping his father.

846
01:07:40,053 --> 01:07:42,982
Mike Damone's
a no-brain little prick, Stacy.

847
01:07:43,052 --> 01:07:45,022
I'm not gonna let him
get away with this.

848
01:07:45,092 --> 01:07:50,354
Linda, please don't do anything.
I don't even like the guy.

849
01:07:50,434 --> 01:07:54,734
Stacy, he's not a guy.
He's a little prick!

850
01:08:23,898 --> 01:08:26,958
Hi, Mikey!

851
01:08:39,280 --> 01:08:41,449
Hi, Damone.

852
01:08:52,431 --> 01:08:55,832
Damone, what went on
between you and Stacy?

853
01:08:55,902 --> 01:09:00,002
Let me tell you something.
Sometimes girls go haywire.

854
01:09:00,072 --> 01:09:04,372
It happened a month ago.
I've been trying to think
of a way to tell you ever since.

855
01:09:04,442 --> 01:09:08,314
We were out... messin' around,
and something happened.

856
01:09:08,384 --> 01:09:11,183
It's over.
It's no big deal.

857
01:09:11,253 --> 01:09:14,184
I never even called her again.

858
01:09:17,224 --> 01:09:19,694
If you ask me,
she's a very aggressive girl.

859
01:09:19,765 --> 01:09:22,595
- Do you understand?
- No, I don't understand.

860
01:09:22,665 --> 01:09:27,036
- She never really was your girlfriend.
- Fuck you, Damone.

861
01:09:27,106 --> 01:09:31,635
There are a lot of girls out there,
and you have to mess around with Stacy?

862
01:09:31,705 --> 01:09:34,236
What do you gotta prove, anyway?

863
01:09:35,147 --> 01:09:37,077
I'm sorry.

864
01:09:37,147 --> 01:09:39,778
I always stick up for you.

865
01:09:39,848 --> 01:09:44,087
Whenever people say, "That Damone, he's
a loudmouth," and they say that a lot,

866
01:09:44,157 --> 01:09:46,918
I always say,
"Hey, you just don't know Damone."

867
01:09:46,998 --> 01:09:50,858
When they call you an idiot,
I say, "Damone's not an idiot.
You just don't know him."

868
01:09:50,928 --> 01:09:55,699
Well, you know something, man?
Maybe they do know you pretty good.

869
01:09:55,769 --> 01:09:57,900
Maybe I'm just finding out now.

870
01:09:57,970 --> 01:09:59,909
Get lost.

871
01:10:03,179 --> 01:10:05,111
You want to do something about it, Rat?

872
01:10:05,181 --> 01:10:08,011
You want to do something about it?
Come on.

873
01:10:08,081 --> 01:10:10,281
- Come on, you wuss!
- Okay. Let's go, man.

874
01:10:10,351 --> 01:10:13,011
- I'll break your fuckin' head off.
- Do something, man.

875
01:10:13,091 --> 01:10:16,652
- A big talker, man!
- Knock this crap off!

876
01:10:16,732 --> 01:10:19,062
Take it somewhere else.

877
01:10:19,132 --> 01:10:21,792
Not in my gym, buddy.

878
01:10:26,173 --> 01:10:29,693
Shit.

879
01:10:32,713 --> 01:10:37,585
Woke up in a great mood.
I don't know what the hell happened.

880
01:10:39,814 --> 01:10:42,375
Come on. Hurry up.
Hurry up.

881
01:10:42,455 --> 01:10:47,625
Today we're going to explore
how this hospital preserves human life.

882
01:10:47,695 --> 01:10:52,026
We'll be visiting every floor
where these fine doctors and nurses...

883
01:10:52,096 --> 01:10:55,797
take care of us in life...
and in death.

884
01:11:03,417 --> 01:11:07,039
Over 30 children
are delivered here each day.

885
01:11:07,119 --> 01:11:09,478
Dr. Kramer to the nurses' station.

886
01:11:09,548 --> 01:11:12,278
- Good morning, Doctor.
- Hi.

887
01:11:12,358 --> 01:11:14,289
Class, this is Dr. Miller.

888
01:11:14,359 --> 01:11:17,419
He'll be joining us
for the last part of our tour today.

889
01:11:17,499 --> 01:11:20,260
If you guys will follow me, please.

890
01:11:22,270 --> 01:11:25,200
I'd like to ask you one last time.

891
01:11:25,270 --> 01:11:29,000
Conduct yourselves
with the utmost maturity.

892
01:11:33,681 --> 01:11:36,702
- You in my class?
- I am today.

893
01:11:45,523 --> 01:11:47,553
-  Yes, Greg?
- Who are these guys?

894
01:11:47,633 --> 01:11:50,063
Most of them are derelicts.

895
01:11:50,133 --> 01:11:53,154
They sold their bodies
to medicine for money.

896
01:11:53,234 --> 01:11:56,675
- About $30, I think?
- Twenty-five.

897
01:11:56,735 --> 01:11:59,004
Righteous bucks!

898
01:11:59,074 --> 01:12:01,404
This gentleman here is named Arthur.

899
01:12:01,474 --> 01:12:04,776
Arthur was good enough
to die last week of heart failure.

900
01:12:04,846 --> 01:12:08,805
We are fortunate today
to view his body...

901
01:12:08,885 --> 01:12:11,376
in its pristine state.

902
01:12:15,527 --> 01:12:17,897
Here an incision has been made.

903
01:12:17,967 --> 01:12:20,027
The ribs have been sawed off,

904
01:12:20,097 --> 01:12:24,968
allowing us to remove
the breastplate...

905
01:12:25,038 --> 01:12:29,568
and really observe the human organs
as they exist in their natural state.

906
01:12:29,638 --> 01:12:31,768
Here we have the human lungs.

907
01:12:32,578 --> 01:12:35,610
And here is the human heart
which, you can see,

908
01:12:35,680 --> 01:12:39,979
is actually located
in the center of your chest.

909
01:12:40,049 --> 01:12:42,520
Ohh! Gnarly!

910
01:12:52,701 --> 01:12:54,732
Are you okay?

911
01:12:54,802 --> 01:12:57,202
Yeah.
I'm fine.

912
01:12:57,272 --> 01:13:00,972
- I just made a jerk out of myself.
- No, you didn't.

913
01:13:01,042 --> 01:13:03,172
Can't go back in there.

914
01:13:03,242 --> 01:13:07,684
Sure. We'll wait until they come out,
and then we'll blend in.

915
01:13:07,753 --> 01:13:10,813
Here they come.

916
01:13:10,893 --> 01:13:12,914
You're so nice.

917
01:14:36,615 --> 01:14:39,915
You should be comin' on pretty soon,
dude. How much did you smoke?

918
01:14:39,985 --> 01:14:43,615
This'll be
a little demonstration of that.

919
01:14:43,695 --> 01:14:45,625
Listen up.

920
01:14:47,395 --> 01:14:50,096
- What was that?
- That was my skull.

921
01:14:50,166 --> 01:14:52,567
-
- I'm so wasted!

922
01:14:52,707 --> 01:14:55,267
Oh, man!

923
01:14:55,337 --> 01:14:58,537
What is this stuff?

924
01:14:58,607 --> 01:15:00,877
Doesn't that stuff
cause brain damage?

925
01:15:00,947 --> 01:15:04,979
- Only if you take it
every day for a month.
- Bitchin'!

926
01:15:05,049 --> 01:15:09,218
- Dude, I'll pick you up in
the van and go to the dance.
- Later.

927
01:15:09,288 --> 01:15:12,049
Jeff, you have company.

928
01:15:12,129 --> 01:15:16,059
Get out of here, Curtis.
I don't hear you unless you knock.

929
01:15:21,400 --> 01:15:23,891
That's better. Entre.

930
01:15:25,811 --> 01:15:27,830
Mr. Hand!

931
01:15:27,910 --> 01:15:31,641
Well, were you going somewhere
tonight, Jeff?

932
01:15:31,711 --> 01:15:33,741
Yeah.
The graduation dance.

933
01:15:33,821 --> 01:15:36,013
It's the last school fiesta
of the year.

934
01:15:36,083 --> 01:15:38,922
Hmm. I'm afraid we've got
some business to discuss here.

935
01:15:38,992 --> 01:15:42,083
Did I do something wrong, Mr. Hand?

936
01:15:42,163 --> 01:15:46,422
According to my calculations,
Mr. Spicoli,

937
01:15:46,492 --> 01:15:51,524
you wasted a total of, uh,
eight hours of my time this year.

938
01:15:51,604 --> 01:15:55,934
And rest assured,
that is a kind estimate.

939
01:15:56,004 --> 01:16:00,174
Now I have the unique pleasure
of squaring our account.

940
01:16:00,244 --> 01:16:05,516
Tonight you and I are going to talk in
great detail about the Davis Agreement,

941
01:16:05,586 --> 01:16:10,286
all the associated treaties, and
the American Revolution in particular.

942
01:16:10,356 --> 01:16:15,227
If you can turn to page 47
of Land of Truth and Liberty.

943
01:16:15,297 --> 01:16:19,567
Oh, I left that book in my locker,
Mr. Hand.

944
01:16:19,638 --> 01:16:23,868
In that case, I'm glad I remembered to
bring an extra copy... just for you.

945
